abstract: An erudite German-born essayist, Mr. Elsaesser was as enthusiastic about the films of Fassbinder as he was about Hollywood melodramas.
snippet: An erudite German-born essayist, Mr. Elsaesser was as enthusiastic about the films of Fassbinder as he was about Hollywood melodramas.
lead_paragraph: Thomas Elsaesser, an influential German-born film scholar and teacher whose writings brimmed with a fascination for Hollywood melodramas, the works of Rainer Werner Fassbinder and Weimar-era movies, died on Dec. 4 in Beijing. He was 76.

abstract: Netflix Inc's animated holiday movie "Klaus" has been watched in nearly 30 million households worldwide during its first month, landing among the streaming service's most-watched original movies, according to data the company provided to Reuters.

abstract: The Van Andel Research Institute, which conducts biomedical research, will pay $5.5 million to resolve civil charges that it failed to disclose to the U.S. government that two of its researchers were funded by Chinese government grants, the Justice Department announced on Thursday.
snippet: The Van Andel Research Institute, which conducts biomedical research, will pay $5.5 million to resolve civil charges that it failed to disclose to the U.S. government that two of its researchers were funded by Chinese government grants, the Justic...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Van Andel Research Institute, which conducts biomedical research, will pay $5.5 million to resolve civil charges that it failed to disclose to the U.S. government that two of its researchers were funded by Chinese government grants, the Justice Department announced on Thursday.
headline_main: Michigan-Based Research Institute to Pay $5.5 Million Over Chinese-Funded Grants
headline_print_headline: Michigan-Based Research Institute to Pay $5.5 Million Over Chinese-Funded Grants

abstract: Concert promoter Live Nation Entertainment Inc agreed to refrain from retaliating against venues that do not use its  Ticketmaster service for every event in a settlement with the U.S. Justice Department, the government said on Thursday.
snippet: Concert promoter Live Nation Entertainment Inc agreed to refrain from retaliating against venues that do not use its  Ticketmaster service for every event in a settlement with the U.S. Justice Department, the government said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Concert promoter Live Nation Entertainment Inc agreed to refrain from retaliating against venues that do not use its Ticketmaster service for every event in a settlement with the U.S. Justice Department, the government said on Thursday.

abstract: U.S. drivers covered 1% more miles in October than a year earlier, traveling a total of 285.1 billion miles (458.8 billion km), the U.S. Department of Transportation said in a monthly report on Thursday.
snippet: U.S. drivers covered 1% more miles in October than a year earlier, traveling a total of 285.1 billion miles (458.8 billion km), the U.S. Department of Transportation said in a monthly report on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. drivers covered 1% more miles in October than a year earlier, traveling a total of 285.1 billion miles (458.8 billion km), the U.S. Department of Transportation said in a monthly report on Thursday.

headline_print_headline: U.S. Drivers Traveled More Miles in October Than a Year Earlier: DOT

abstract: The U.S. Senate, rushing to meet a looming deadline, approved and sent to President Donald Trump a $1.4 trillion package of fiscal 2020 spending bills that would end prospects of government shutdowns at week's end when temporary funding expires.
snippet: The U.S. Senate, rushing to meet a looming deadline, approved and sent to President Donald Trump a $1.4 trillion package of fiscal 2020 spending bills that would end prospects of government shutdowns at week's end when temporary funding expires.
